8/Math/MathML\"><mi>Al</mi></math>.</p><p>Bur&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Al</mi></math>&nbsp;belongs to the p-block element and it has ability to show its covalency&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;and form polymeric covalent compounds. But&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Be</mi></math>&nbsp;is very small in size, it can expand its covalency only up to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024aa469321ec08c68901", "616024a9237a25efd60dbdcd", "616024abc6f1502002a3dc2c", "616024a89f964d9d52aa6b8b", "61e7bd7aab48fb79284bc3e3", "61c089a7663468b6d34550ff", "61bb82214bce2ad876fca9c2", "616024aa213c13ef429d5b4e", "61964ca2710d67856e992fc6", "61964ca1dcc5b1804ff140aa", "629f3a8744592a265aea99f0", "629109e05957314a979d27d7", "629f39014329d080bbbb2088", "6296211a6059fd63d273c98e", "64eb06c93118f713ecfef0d6", "66d5853da75f05ee8564f588", "67921d971d5b5072da5e9c5a", "68091fea3a10446a207fdc42"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}